OL,5, Two survivors of the 1921 massacre of  
OL,6, black people in the US city of Tulsa   
OL,7, have been granted Ghanaian citizenship.
OL,9,FViola Fletcher, 108 and her brother    
OL,10,FHughes Van Ellis, 102, are two of three
OL,11,Fliving survivors.                      
OL,13,FAbout 300 black residents of Greenwood 
OL,14,F- a prosperous town then known as      
OL,15,F"Black Wall Street" - were murdered and
OL,16,Ftheir homes and businesses destroyed by
OL,17,Fa mob of white people.                 
OL,19,FThe citizenship ceremony took place at 
OL,20,FGhana's embassy in Washington DC.      
